narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Great way to fulfill the senior psych requirement. 20+ page lit review for the semester.

I would recommend this course for someone who has found a topic of interest in another Yale course or elsewhere that no other class allows an in depth exploration of. I would not recommend this course to someone that is not internally driven and motivated as there are few if any check in points weekly or monthly to make sure you keep on top of your work.
Well, it's directed reading, so it is pretty much precisely what you make of it. I had a ball.
Complete liberty to read/write whatever you want. Great if you have ideas in mind that the available classes don't otherwise cater to.
Yes, it's a great way to finish your senior requirement.
